\'93Xanthus, and you Podargus, Aithus,\uc0\u8232 noble Lampus! Now\'92s the time to pay me back\u8232 for all my care, all the sweet grain you\'92ve had\u8232 from Andromache, great E\'ebtion\'92s daughter,\u8232 for the wine she\'92s mixed for you to drink,\u8232 whenever you desired. She took care of you,\u8232 even before me, her own fine husband.\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[190]\u8232 Come on then, go after them with speed,\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0220\u8232 so we may capture Nestor\'92s shield, whose fame\u8232 extends right up to heaven\'97it\'92s all gold\'97\u8232 the shield itself, cross braces, too.\u8232 From horse-taming Diomedes\'92 shoulders\u8232 we\'92ll strip the decorated body armour,\u8232 a work created by Hephaestus.\u8232 I think if we could capture these two things,\u8232 Achaeans would climb aboard their ships tonight.\'94\
