0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0320\u8232 Orsilochus died first, then Ormenus, Ophelestes,\u8232 Daitor, Chromius, godlike Lycophontes,\u8232 Amopaon, son of Polyaimon, and Melanippus\'97\u8232 all these Teucer dropped one by one on fertile earth.\u8232 Watching him cause havoc with his bow in Trojan ranks,\u8232 Agamemnon, king of men, was overjoyed.\u8232 He went up, stood beside him, then spoke out:\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0[280]\
